Create a Kernel project
=======================

To create a new Kernel project, Go to File > New > Project... and select Kernel project under Ac6 Tools folder. Then click on the Next button to open the wizard.

.. image:: ../images/gettingstarted/kernel/kernelimg1.png

On the next page, enter the new project name (such as “my_kernel”) then click on Next button. You can choose the location of your project but it is recommended to use the default location. 

.. image:: ../images/gettingstarted/kernel/kernelimg2.png

On project configuration page, enter where the sources are located. Select Directory if the source is in a directory. Select Archive if the source is in a tarball archive. Enter the cross-compiler. 

.. image:: ../images/gettingstarted/kernel/kernelimg3.png
